  "prompt": "How long do Acer laptops usually last?",
  "response": "The lifespan of an Acer laptop, like most laptops, can vary based on several factors, including the model, usage patterns, maintenance, and build quality. On average, a typical Acer laptop can last anywhere from 3 to 5 years. Higher-end models or gaming laptops, which tend to have more robust hardware, might last longer, potentially 5 to 7 years, if well-maintained. However, over time, users might experience performance issues as software demands increase or hardware components wear out. Proper maintenance, such as keeping the laptop clean, ensuring adequate ventilation, and running regular software updates, can help extend its lifespan.",
